    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal parallel lines. A vertical arrow pointing downward to the middle of the lines is labeled Incident Light. The medium above the top line is Air. The medium between the two lines is Thin Film, where n equals 1.40. The medium below the bottom line is Glass Lens, where n equals 1.50.\" src=\"/images/ae789904dc3031ee00e008e8dd3eeb74.svg\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A glass lens with an index of refraction of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.50\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1.50\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.50</mn></math></span></span> has a thin coating of film with an index of refraction of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.40\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1.40\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.40</mn></math></span></span> on the top surface of the lens, as shown in the figure. When light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"700 nanometers\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"700 nanometers\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>700</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>nm</mi></math></span></span> is incident on the film normal to the surface, there is maximum destructive interference between the light reflected from the air-film and film-glass interfaces. What is the minimum possible thickness of the film?</p>\n",
